    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-03T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-03T15:00:00-05:00" n="157"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d157">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/9799a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d157fn1">The same, on the same date, to the
                        Ambassadors in France (No. 3830) and Italy (No. 1248).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-03T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 3, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7556. There is a well-defined movement in Congress to declare that a state of war
                    exists between the United States and Turkey and Bulgaria. Will you please
                    confidentially sound the Government to which you are accredited and obtain its
                    opinion as to the advisability of such a declaration against both or either of
                    the countries named. You will perceive that the action of the United States is
                    based essentially on expediency. I desire therefore to know the judgment of the
                    Government to which you are accredited, as to whether or not such a declaration
                    would be of material aid to the supreme purpose of defeating the Central Powers.
                    A reply as soon as possible is desired.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
